## 1. GLOBAL UI & DESIGN PRINCIPLES

* **Shape:** Rounded cards, buttons, inputs — min radius 12px; no sharp corners.
* **Color:** Soft pastels (light blue `#5B8DEF`, soft yellow `#F5B84C`, mint `#B8E6D5`, lavender `#D4C5F9`); success/error in muted tones.
* **Hierarchy:** One clear primary action per screen; titles 1.3–1.5× body size; ample whitespace (16–24px between sections).
* **Typography:** Large, readable fonts for children (18–22px body); rounded sans-serif (Nunito, Quicksand, or similar).
* **Motion:** Subtle only — gentle hover lift (2–4px), soft fade/slide; no flashing, no aggressive parallax; reduce-motion respected.
* **Contrast:** Text on background ≥ 4.5:1 (WCAG AA); interactive elements clearly focusable.
* **Feedback:** Always encouraging; “Try again” / “Almost!” instead of “Wrong”; no punitive visuals or sounds.
* **AI:** Hints and adaptations feel like a friendly helper; no “AI” branding in child-facing UI.

