## 3. AUTHENTICATION UI

### Login / Register Screen
* **Layout:** Centered card on `#F8FAFC`; card max-width 420px; padding 40px; radius 20px; shadow modal-level.
* **Tabs:** “Child” | “Parent / Educator” | “Admin” — pill or underline; 16px; active state with primary color; Admin tab visually subdued or behind “Admin?” link.

### Child Login / Sign-up
* **Nickname:** Single input, 48px height, 16px font, placeholder “Your nickname”; optional helper “Parents can add a password later.”
* **Avatar:** Grid of 8–12 avatars; each 56px, 12px gap; selected state: 3px ring `#5B8DEF`; click/tap to select.
* **Optional password:** Collapsible “Add password” (parent-controlled); same input style.
* **Submit:** “Start playing” — full-width, 48px height, primary button.

### Parent / Admin Login
* **Email + Password:** Two inputs, 48px height each, 16px font; 16px spacing between.
* **Forgot password:** Link under password, 14px, `#5B8DEF`.
* **Submit:** “Log in” — full-width, 48px.
* **Error message:** Below submit; soft red background `#FEE2E2`, text `#B91C1C`, 14px; icon optional; no harsh wording.

### UX Rules
* Copy: “Welcome back!” / “Choose your avatar” — warm and simple.
* Errors: “This password doesn’t match” rather than “Invalid credentials.”
* Role separation: Clear labels so a child doesn’t land on admin form by mistake.

