## 5. STORY READING SCREEN

### Layout
* **Header:** Story title 20px; progress indicator (e.g. “Page 2 of 5” or step dots); back button left; height 56px.
* **Content area:** Max-width 720px, centered; padding 24px.
* **Story text:** Font 20–22px (child body); line-height 1.7; paragraph spacing 24px; color `#2D3748`.
* **Background:** Soft tint per “mood” (e.g. warm for adventure, cool for mystery) — very subtle; e.g. `#FFF9F0` or `#F0F9FF`.

### Audio Controls
* **Position:** Fixed bottom-right or inline under title.
* **Play / Pause:** Icon button 48px; state clear (playing = pause icon).
* **Speed:** “Slow” | “Normal” — toggle or dropdown; 14px label.

### Navigation
* **“Next” button:** Appears after a minimum reading time (e.g. 3–5 s) or on scroll-to-end; primary button; 48px height.
* **Transition:** Fade or short slide (300ms) to next page; no hard cut.

### First page vs. mid-story
* **First page:** Optional story cover image (max-height 200px, radius 16px); title 24px; 1–2 sentence “What you’ll discover” teaser; “Start reading” CTA.
* **Mid pages:** Text only (or inline illustration); same typography and spacing; no repeat of title in body.

### End-of-story / chapter complete
* **Screen:** Full card or full-width section; “You finished this part!” — 24px; optional illustration (trophy or book closed).
* **Summary:** “You solved X riddles”; stars earned this story (e.g. ⭐⭐⭐); optional “See your new badge” if unlocked.
* **Actions:** “Next story” (primary) and “Back to my stories” (secondary); 48px buttons; 24px gap.
* **Transition:** Optional short celebration (stars float up); then route to story map or next story intro.

