## 6. RIDDLE INTERACTION SCREEN

### Riddle Card
* **Container:** Centered card; max-width 560px; padding 32px; radius 16px; shadow card.
* **Riddle text:** 22px font; line-height 1.5; optional decorative quote or icon.
* **Illustration:** Optional; above or beside text; max-height 160px; radius 12px.

### Answer Input
* **Text input:** Large; 56px height (mobile), 48px (desktop); 18px font; placeholder “Type your answer”; radius 12px; border 2px, focus ring primary.
* **OR multiple choice:** 2–4 option cards; each min 48px height; 16px padding; radius 12px; border default; selected = primary border + light fill.
* **Submit:** “Check answer” or “Submit” — full-width or right-aligned; 48px height; primary button; disabled until input exists.

### Feedback States
* **Correct:** Short confetti or star burst (subtle); “Well done!” / “You got it!”; success color; optional star; auto-advance after 1.5–2 s or “Next” button.
* **Almost correct:** “You’re so close!”; “Almost correct” color; one gentle hint line; “Try again” keeps input focused.
* **Incorrect:** “Not quite — want a hint?”; gentle tone; “Get a hint” button becomes enabled; no red flash; input remains editable.

### Transition: story → riddle
* **Bridge screen (optional):** Short line “Ready for a riddle?” or “Can you guess?”; 20px; optional illustration (lightbulb or question mark); “Show riddle” button; 1–2 s then auto-advance or on tap.
* **Alternative:** Riddle card fades in directly after last story paragraph; no separate screen.

### Transition: riddle correct → next
* **After “Well done!”:** 1.5–2 s display then “Next” appears; or auto-advance to next riddle / end-of-story after 2 s.
* **Next riddle:** Same layout; riddle card content swaps; optional “Riddle 2 of 3” indicator at top.

