## 12. ACCESSIBILITY & UX RULES

* **High contrast:** Optional theme or system preference; ensure 4.5:1 (or 3:1 for large text).
* **Keyboard:** All interactive elements focusable; visible focus ring (2px primary); logical tab order; no trap in modals (Escape closes).
* **Screen reader:** Landmarks, headings, button labels; “Submit answer” not just “Submit”; hint content announced when opened.
* **Audio:** TTS toggle; captions or transcript for any audio hints.
* **Language:** Short sentences; avoid jargon in child-facing copy.
* **Reinforcement:** No “Wrong!” or “Fail”; use “Not quite” and “Try again” / “Get a hint.”
* **Safety:** No external links in child flow without parent gate; no chat; no user-generated content visible to children without moderation.

